Very likely final answer

The query returned nothing because the join between:

CASENET.PROVIDER.PROVIDER_ID

and

BI_ANALYSIS.DIM_PROVIDER_SPECIALTY.PROVIDER_ID

is probably not the correct relationship.

The column names match, but the underlying IDs may be different business keys.

A better troubleshooting query

Use this one now:

SELECT
    p.PROVIDER_ID,
    TRY_TO_NUMBER(p.PROVIDER_ID) AS PROVIDER_ID_NUM,
    p.PROVIDER_NAME,
    p.NPI,
    s.PROVIDER_ID AS SPEC_PROVIDER_ID,
    s.PROVIDER_SPECIALTY_CODE,
    s.ACTIVE_FLAG AS SPEC_ACTIVE_FLAG
FROM FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.CASENET.PROVIDER p
LEFT JOIN FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.DIM_PROVIDER_SPECIALTY s
    ON TRY_TO_NUMBER(p.PROVIDER_ID) = s.PROVIDER_ID
LIMIT 100;

If SPEC_PROVIDER_ID is null for every row, then that join is wrong.

